Understood — you want a **brand new concept**, different scene, different model. The Concept 12 brief was just context/reference for the brand world.

Let me collect what I need for the new concept.{
  "question": "What direction do you want to go for this new concept?",
  "follow_up": [
    {
      "description": "I have a specific scene, model, and vibe already in mind — let me write it out.",
      "label": "Give me the full brief"
    },
    {
      "description": "Surprise me — pick a completely different scene, model type, and mood that fits the iSupply beach-tech world but hasn't been done in the set yet.",
      "label": "Director decides"
    },
    {
      "description": "Show me 3 distinct concept directions to choose from — different settings, different model energy, different moods.",
      "label": "Give me options"
    }
  ]
}

On it. Let me build something that earns its place in the set.{
  "question": "One quick parameter before I build — what aspect ratio for this concept?",
  "follow_up": [
    {
      "description": "4:5 ratio — same as Concept 12, consistent with the carousel set.",
      "label": "4:5 (Instagram feed portrait)"
    },
    {
      "description": "1:1 ratio — clean square format, works across all platforms.",
      "label": "1:1 (Square)"
    },
    {
      "description": "9:16 ratio — vertical full-screen for Stories, Reels, TikTok.",
      "label": "9:16 (Stories / Reels)"
    },
    {
      "description": "Pick the ratio that best serves the concept you build.",
      "label": "Director decides"
    }
  ]
}
